IT TECHNICIAN:
This is a sales, customer service, repair/install, and commission based position.
Please visit our website to learn more about our company.

Non-exempt, full-time, benefits
Hourly base wage dependent on City minimum wage and experience
Additional earnings of overtime and commission – earnings upwards of $100k annually
Requirements:
Provide eligibility to work in the USA
Consent to background check
Possess California Driver’s License and provide clean DMV record.
Must be living within the area of our stores.

Some software and hardware troubleshooting, of devices, repair, upgrade or install, such as but not required to know all of the following:
Windows OS devices and software,
Apple OS devices and software,
Chome OS devices and software.
Some experience with network setup, troubleshoot, or installation.
Have customer service experience with sales and comfortable working on commission.
The IT Technician will receive devices from customers, listen and discuss the problems with customers, diagnosis, and provide appropriate steps for troubleshooting. IT Technicians will also run diagnostic tools on Apple, Android, and Windows devices, networks, or other devices and present options to customers, take appropriate actions based on response from customers in need of repair, replacing or upgrading parts, or replacing entirely their device. Follow the appropriate standards of operation from check-in to resolution to check-out process.
A candidate will possess some or all the following experience/skills: The following duties are normal for this position. These are not to be construed as exclusive or all-inclusive.
Other duties may be required and assigned.
Create a first-rate customer experience
Knowledgeable on latest diagnostic tools for computers
Understands parts of systems and able to identify computer components
Networking – onsite jobs; homes, businesses, servers
Set-up servers and set-up of Networks and/or troubleshooting networks
Repair, replace, upgrade hardware within the device
Install operating systems and software, programs, MS Office, financial programs, web browsers, email clients, etc.
Knowledgeable regarding virus detection protocols and programs
Manages deadlines and multiple priorities simultaneously
Create invoices through Company ExtraNet system, breakdown pricing as needed per customer requests
Accept payments from customers for services
Sales of PCs, Macs and OS software
Create Worker Orders, Purchase Orders, and Invoices
Respond to email questions entered on website
Answer customer telephone calls, utilizing scripts as provided

Job Title: IT Helpdesk Support Level II Technician
Job Description:
BCS365 is a top, growing Managed Service Provider (MSP). Join our growing team!

This is a full-time position: Monday - Friday, 12:00 PM - 9:00 PM
The primary responsibilities for this position are handling second level support in Client Services team. Respond, troubleshoot and generate and update service tickets for BCS365 clients. The technology includes but is not limited to enterprise Voice, Data, Video, Wireless, Cloud, and Security.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities
Information Technology Support (ITS) relating to desktop technical issues involving Microsoft’s core business applications, operating systems for PC (Windows 7+), MAC (OS X) and peripherals.
Responsible for technical break/fix support for all Information Technology Support (ITS) systems currently deployed in production.
Interface and maintain effective communication with business users and other ITS team members when analyzing, updating and resolving tickets.
Responsible for administration, maintenance and second level support of back-end global ITS systems.
Identification of opportunities for continuous improvement (upgrades, security and update patches, etc.) of systems in production.
Communication with customers as required: keeping them informed properly in ticketing system of incident or request progress and notifying them of impending changes base on client’s SLA.
Escalate client support tickets to appropriate resource following the escalation process and procedures
Work with Dispatchers and Team Leads to ensure requests are routed to the proper resource in order to be resolved quickly and efficiently.
Data entry may be required for new and active clients on Ticketing system.
Responsible for entering time and all work with proper updates in Ticketing system as it occurs.
Identify proactive ways to reduce the number of issues and support calls in the environment (reduction in quality, interruption or failure of an ITS service).
On-call rotation.
Other duties as assigned.

Customer Focus
Demonstrate exceptional customer service skills in order to exceed customers’ expectations and to minimize escalations by taking ownership of customer reported issues.
Illustrated diplomacy, tactfulness and empathy when dealing with customers
Exemplified ability to defuse escalations and high-tension situations
Well-developed ability to appease customers experiencing service outages and difficulties
Ability to listen actively and ask clarifying questions to seek understanding
Experience going above and beyond duty to delight customers
Must have a genuine drive for customer satisfaction and retention

Required Professional IT Certifications and Experience
Education: Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or related field
IT Experience: 3 years minimum
Previous MSP experience, or experience supporting external customer base required
One or more of the following: CompTIA or A+, Network+, Microsoft MCP
Advanced understanding of operating systems (Windows 7 or higher and MAC OS X), printing systems, network topology, Linux/Unix command
Continually advancing your knowledge base through certification courses.

Decision making and Self-Management
Interface and maintain effective communication with business users and other ITS team members when analyzing, updating and resolving tickets.
Skills in troubleshooting, solving problems and root cause analysis.
Excellent organizational and time management skills. Capability to manage own workload while meeting team goals and business needs of the company.
Proven aptitude to work well in a team or independently with minimum supervision.
Desire and capability to work and make timely decisions in a rapidly changing and uncertain environment.

Troubleshooting
Ability to troubleshoot complex problems, analyze possible root causes and educate customers to perform troubleshooting
Broad knowledge to assist customers with troubleshooting customer equipment (CPE, computers), inside wiring (IW) and using their products and services

*Must be able to lift up to 30 pounds.
*Please Note: BCS365 participates in E-Verify and will provide the federal government with your Form I-9 information to confirm that you are authorized to work in the U.S.

Turn your craft into a prosperous career! Join our team of field professional technicians to learn new skills, work with great people, and be rewarded for your knowledge at PREVENT.

United Site Services (USS) makes things happen. From building a skyscraper or new home community to providing services to America's largest music festivals, USS is there every step of the way.
As the industry leader in portable sanitation services, we deliver the best for our customers. But to do that, we need the best people to join our team. That's where you come in!
Position Description*
Apply to open positions at United Site Services text USS Careers to 22633 to get started!*
PURPOSE*: This position coordinates and oversees the activities of associates in the Fence department engaged in installation/repair of fence products. Work is performed under general direction of the branch Fence Supervisor or Manager.
RESPONSIBILITIES*:
Coordinates work activity for Fence Technicians, Fence Helpers, and Fence Branch associates; participates in the work as needed. Oversees the fence branch.
Estimates the time and material costs required for projected fence jobs; keeps cost and job records and submits reports; initiates requisitions for supplies, tools, and equipment.
Conducts periodic inspections and gives on-site supervision over hazardous or unusual work assignments; assures availability of equipment, materials, and supplies.
Trains and instructs fence department associates on detailed procedures.
Participates in the counseling/coaching and recruiting/staffing process.
Trains personnel in the safe operation of equipment and tools.
Conducts safety tailgates meetings/maintains training records and helps to enforce safety regulations, rules, and working conditions.
Conduct daily pre-shift vehicle inspection & report deficiencies to shop immediately. Conduct daily inspection of all tools assigned to the truck to ensure safety and proper working condition.
Check loads to ensure that truck has all material (fence panels, poles, etc.) and tools needed to complete service tickets.
Meet with site superintendent (or other designated representative) to confirm work order. Maintain telephone or radio contact with supervisor to receive additional instructions, changes to work locations, etc.
Unload all fence materials and install fence panels, with appropriate tools, at work site in accordance with pre-determined specifications. Locate, measure and mark location for placement of panels & installation.
Coordinate the workload and the efforts of the fence helper. Examine and inspect work progress, equipment & work site to ensure that specifications are met.
Records information such as personnel, production and operational data on specified forms and submit to Fence Manager at end of each shift.
Follows all established safety rules & regulations.
Special projects as assigned by management.
Operate fence vehicle to and from pre-designated work sites.
Requirements*
HS Diploma or general education degree (GED) and 1 to 3 years general labor experience; or equivalent combination of education and experience.
Must have a minimum of 12 months professional driving experience.
Computer knowledge (Navision, Microsoft Office & routing/logistics software).
Excellent written and verbal communication skills.
Knowledge of all company assets in inventory.
Knowledge of proper cleaning & repair of those assets.
Ability to multi-task and work independently while being safety conscious.
Ability to give others direction
What's in it for you?*
At United Site Services, we provide a competitive benefits package that lets you live life the way you intend. We offer so much more than a regular paycheck; our benefits package is chock full of perks such as paid time off, healthcare, 401K matching, employee assistance programs, Life and AD&D insurance and much more!
Please *click here* to learn more about United Site Services!

JOB DESCRIPTION*
TITLE: * Refrigeration Mechanic/Technician or Refrigeration Trainee
DEPARTMENT: * Refrigeration (085)
REPORTS TO: * Refrigeration Manager
FLSA: * Non-exempt Hourly
Position Summary*
Christopher Ranch stores, processes, packs and ships garlic out of its headquarters located in Gilroy California. These processes are all enabled by multiple teams of fabricators, electricians, mechanics and operators.

The primary duties of this position revolve around maintaining the proper operation and upkeep of ammonia and freon refrigeration systems.
Open Positions*
Christopher Ranch is looking to recruit both experienced Refrigeration Mechanics and Refrigeration Trainees. Candidates with a refrigeration background are highly welcome. Candidates with a general mechanical or electrical background, who have an interest in learning refrigeration, are also encouraged to apply.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities*
The essential functions include, but are not limited to the following:

· Complete regular daily, weekly and monthly inspections.

· Troubleshoot abnormalities within the refrigeration system; These issues range wildly in scope, but are most often related to mechanical refrigeration components or electrical control issues.

· Complete regular preventative maintenance services on evaporators, condensers, valves, electrical cabinets, safety resources and other related equipment.

· Seek out and report potential problems or safety hazards and actively participate in mitigation and repairs as required.

· Respond quickly and efficiently to reported breakdowns – on rare occasions this could also include responding during unscheduled hours.

· Maintain regular logs of equipment maintenance, repairs and inspections.

· Communicate often and clearly with teammates, vendors and department manager.

· Maintain company resources in a respectful and organized manner - clean workspaces, put away tools, maintain department resources and preform facility repairs as required.
Safety*
Christopher Ranch places safety as its highest concern;

· *Response* *Team*: All refrigeration team members are required to participate as a member of the company’s emergency response team; this includes responding to emergency situations and participating in regular drills. Employees are required to complete all assignments in a way that complies with all government regulations and company policies, including; GMPS, OSHA, EPA, HIPPA…

· *Communication*: Report unsafe equipment or other hazards to management for repairs.

· *Upkeep*: Maintain safety resources, including; respirators, safety showers and fire prevention resources.
Minimum Qualifications (Education, Experience, Skills)*
To be successful in this position, a qualified candidate will have;
High school diploma or GED.
A good command of the English language, both written and spoken.
Basic digital communication skills; smartphones, email and text messaging
Proficiency with hand tools including; wrenches, drills, hammers, screwdrivers…
Experience troubleshooting basic electrical glitches.
Desired Qualifications (Education, Experience, Skills)*
Experience with ammonia refrigeration systems, preferably in an agricultural/production facility.
Technical Training Certification, or Degree
RETA or other Ammonia Refrigeration Certification
EPA 608 Universal Freon Certification
Experience with Freon Refrigeration Systems (In particular refrigerants R22, R407 and R512)
Reporting Conditions*
Typical work weeks are Monday through Friday, eight hours a day.

o Start times will be assigned within the range of 6:00am-8:00am.

o Each mechanic is also required to work one Saturday a month for routine inspections.

Atypical work weeks can exist due to pre-scheduled projects or emergency conditions.

o These circumstances can trigger mandatory overtime and weekend work.

o Christopher Ranch will make a good faith effort to schedule all projects in advance and give ample notification. However, emergency conditions do arise. Employees are expected to make reasonable accommodations to be available for unscheduled and urgent situations.

As assigned, Mechanics can be asked to “cover alarms.”

o This means being available during off-hours to respond to computer-generated alarm notifications.

o This might also include either responding in person to the job site, or by dispatching a team-mate to the job site.
Physical Demands and Work Environment*
The description of the physical demands and the work environment characteristics here represent those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform and those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this position. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to talk or hear. The employee frequently is required to stand. The employee is occasionally required to sit; walk; climb ladders and stairs; use hands to finger, handle, or feel; reach with hands and arms; climb or balance; and stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The employee must frequently lift and/or move up to 10 pounds and occasionally lift and/or move up to 25 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, color vision, and ability to adjust focus.

While performing the duties of this job, the employee is exposed to plant environment to include moving mechanical parts, fumes or airborne particles, toxic or caustic chemicals, risk of electrical shock, and explosives. Safety Glasses must be worn at all times. The noise level in the work environment is usually moderate.

This job description in no way states or implies that these are the only duties to be performed by the employee(s) incumbent in this position. Employees will be required to follow any other job-related instructions and to perform any other job-related duties requested by any person authorized to give instructions or assignments.

All duties and responsibilities are essential functions and requirements and are subject to possible modification to reasonably accommodate individuals with disabilities. To perform this job successfully, the incumbents will posses the skills aptitudes and abilities to perform each duty proficiently. Some requirements may exclude individuals who pose a direct threat or significant risk to the health or safety of themselves or others. The requirements listed in this document are the minimum levels of knowledge, skills or abilities.

This document does not create an employment contract, implied or otherwise, other than an “at will” relationship.

Company Description:

Steeped, Inc. is an exciting new coffee company that focuses on purpose as well as profits. Steeped is operating in the high-growth specialty coffee and single-serve coffee spaces - using innovation to bring these two markets together for the first time. The company is located in Scotts Valley, CA (in the Santa Cruz area) and has developed a proprietary single-serve coffee method that is brewed in bags, like tea, but is made from renewable and compostable materials. Steeped sells directly under the Steeped Coffee brand to B2C and B2B distribution channels, while also licensing the Steeped Brewing Method and technology to a growing list of national and international coffee roasters and other private label partners. Steeped is experiencing exciting growth and adoption across the country.

We are a Benefit Corporation and B Corp Certified and focused on Purpose Beyond Profit. We believe that business can be done without compromise. Our Mission includes being good stewards of the planet and loving people. All of our current packaging is made with compostable and renewable materials, and our coffee is ethically sourced and directly traded—yet we are always searching for new ways to improve and innovate.
The *RECEIVING TECHNICIAN* POSITION is a key position in our Fulfillment and Manufacturing Departments. This individual is responsible for assisting with the receipt of all incoming goods of all Steeped brand and licensed partner products, as well as other fulfillment initiatives.
Department Structure: Reports to Director of Logistics/Fulfillment and Fulfillment Coordinator

ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Maintains product assurance through Steeped Coffee’s defined quality standards and GMP practices
Have clear knowledge of all safety, quality, and sanitation policies, procedures, and guidelines
Proactively communicate and work towards fulfillment/manufacturing and company goals
Ensure warehousing space is kept clean and organized to Steeped standards at all times
Responsibly operate and manage material handling and warehousing equipment
Ability to work independently and with a team to problem solve on the fly
Completes the intake of product in a timely manner that supports manufacturing and shipping departments.
Accurately fill, assemble and manage all outgoing orders
Complete all assigned tasks and responsibilities by end of a shift
Have clear knowledge of all packaging materials and equipment

We offer an array of mental health services to adults with serious mental illness. We partner with public sector entities and behavioral health organizations and have over 130 programs and over 4,000 employees across the country. And we're growing all the time! When you work at Telecare, you help to empower thousands of individuals every day in their journeys of recovery.

Telecare is proud to have been recognized by The Bay Area Business Times as the 9th Best Place To Work In the Bay Area for 2020! This is the 18th time we have made the list!

As a part of the Telecare Family, Heritage Psychiatric Health Facility (PHF) is a 26-bed hospital providing acute psychiatric treatment to adults over the age of 18.

Employment Status: Full-Time

Shift: Varies as needed

Days: Varies as needed

POSITION SUMMARY

The Recovery Specialist II provides care that responds to the physical and psychological needs of members served. The Recovery Specialist II provides direct and indirect services according to individual service plans and Medicaid standards.

QUALIFICATIONS

Required:

• High school diploma or G.E.D and two (2) years of experience in a psychiatric mental health setting or BA/BS with one (1) year experience in mental health setting

• Knowledge of basic nursing skills and interventions, as well as mental and physical health conditions and terminologies

• Certification as a CNA or its equivalent is acceptable documentation of nursing skills knowledge

• Must be at least 18 years of age

• Must be CPR, Crisis Prevention Institute (CPI), and First Aid certified on date of employment or within 60 days of employment and maintain current certification throughout employment

• All opportunities at Telecare are contingent upon successful completion and receipt of acceptable results of the applicable post-offer physical examination, 2-step PPD test for tuberculosis, acceptable criminal background clearances, excluded party sanctions, and degree or license verification. If the position requires driving, valid driver’s license, a motor vehicle clearance and proof of auto insurance is required at time of employment and must be maintained throughout employment. Additional regulatory, contractual or local requirements may apply

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

• Demonstrates the Telecare mission, purpose, values, and beliefs in everyday language and contact with the internal and external stakeholders

• Provides safe, effective, and efficient implementation of direct care in accordance with established policies, procedures, and standards of care

• Establishes, maintains, and co-facilitates a therapeutic relationship with members served; acts as a role model by maintaining a hopeful and positive attitude and problem solving and coping with mental illness

• Attends and participates in community meetings and groups

• Charts and observes client behavior

• Documents client activities of daily living, response to interventions, and significant behavior changes as appropriate

• Admits and discharges members served as assigned; including completing associated documentation

• Collects stool, urine and other specimens, as requested, on assigned clients

• Obtains client vital signs and weights, as assigned

• Assists members served with hygienic care

• Assists at mealtime by distributing meal trays, pouring beverages, and/or feeding members served in need of assistance

• Provides client monitoring including, but not limited to, rounds, seclusion and restraint supervision and smoke breaks.

• Assists in client outings, which may include driving.

• Practices body substance precautions at all times

• Must assist with restraint of members served in the event of assaultive behavior and pass assault crisis/crisis prevention training

Duties and responsibilities may be added, deleted and/or changed at the discretion of management.

SKILLS

• Knowledge of basic psychiatric rehabilitation interventions

• Good communication skills

• Ability to use problem-solving techniques

• Ability to interview members served to determine client needs

PHYSICAL DEMANDS

The physical demands here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.

The employee is occasionally required to sit, bend, squat, kneel, crawl, twist, push, pull and lift and carry items weighing 50 pounds or less as well as to frequently walk, stand, twist, reach and to do simple and power grasping. The position requires manual deviation, repetitive and dexterity and be exposed to uneven walking ground as well as Hazardous Exposure (Blood Borne Pathogens, Hospital Waste, Chemical & Infectious).

GRAIL is a healthcare company whose mission is to detect cancer early, when it can be cured. GRAIL is focused on alleviating the global burden of cancer by developing pioneering technology to detect and identify multiple deadly cancer types early. The company is using the power of next-generation sequencing, population-scale clinical studies, and state-of-the-art computer science and data science to enhance the scientific understanding of cancer biology, and to develop its multi-cancer early detection blood test. GRAIL is headquartered in Menlo Park, CA with locations in Washington, D.C., North Carolina, and the United Kingdom. It is supported by leading global investors and pharmaceutical, technology, and healthcare companies. For more information, please visit www.grail.com.

GRAIL is seeking a Laboratory Technician I/II for the R&D Laboratory Management team, who will be primarily responsible for ensuring the efficient operation of GRAIL Research and Development activities. The ideal candidate is a detail-oriented, dynamic team player with experience in both automated and manual molecular biology workflows combined with strong interest in NGS methodologies. The candidate will be expected to partner with many functions of our organization - Automation, Product Development, LIMS, Supply Chain, Biosample Operations, and Clinical Lab - to ensure the successful completion of R&D projects and general Operational support.
You Will:
Execute and monitor regular maintenance of laboratory equipment.
Perform inventory control compliant with 5S methodology.
Maintain laboratory cleanliness in compliance with the Hygiene Plan.
Draft and review operational documentation.
Execute on automated and manual sample preparation and NGS assays.
Ensure laboratory activities are performed in compliance with procedures and safety guidelines when handling, storing and disposing of hazardous or bio-hazardous materials.
Perform data analysis and present it to small and large teams.
Be responsible for accurately recording work performed per GLP, including results and methodology.
Have excellent personal task management skills and a high level of self-motivation.

Your Background Should Include:

B.S required in a relevant scientific field.
1-5 years of experience in basic molecular biology laboratory techniques.
Familiarity with nucleic acid handling (e.g., SPRI and PCR) and quantification techniques (e.g., Nanodrop, Bioanalyzer, Fragment Analyzer, ddPCR).
Familiarity with manual and automated NGS protocols.
Experience with Automated sample preparation workflows is a plus.
Excellent teamwork and collaboration skills.
Project management and organizational skills.
Outstanding written and verbal communication skills.
Self-directed, innovative, and creative thinker.
General computer skills and proficiency in GSuite.

Pharmacy Technician, Bilingual*
Our Client is the leader in managing complex population health, concentrating on all areas across healthcare and pharmaceutical management. 10,000 people wake up every day determined to help our members. We do this by connecting behavioral, physical, pharmacy and social needs into a complete picture of care that’s personalized, coordinated and cost-effective. By turning fragmented care into focused care, we empower 1 in 10 Americans to lead healthier, more vibrant lives.
ATTAC Groups client is a next-generation, full-service pharmacy benefit manager (PBM) that moves beyond the basic services to help our customers and members solve complex pharmacy challenges. We do this by connecting them to the people, technology and information they need to make smarter healthcare decisions. As experts in pharmacy management, we discover new and better ways to help clients manage the rising cost of specialty medications, ensure members adhere to their medications, and provide prescribers access to the resources they need to make more informed health decisions for their patients.
This is an exciting opportunity for a *Pharmacy Technician* to work in a complex, high impact customer service role for our Member Services department. The Pharmacy Technician accepts incoming calls related to requests and resolves issues that have been submitted via phone and fax, and partners with other departments to ensure timely resolution of requests/inquiries, which include: Pharmacy, Shipping, Customer Care, Finance, Claims Processing, and Eligibility. This position may work in multiple types of queues and databases to resolve issues. This position also involves extensive phone interactions with members and possibly Prescribers as well. Technicians will serve as the initial point of contact for Customer Care Associates and Members before the required Pharmacist involvement for all clinical issues/questions.
This role is both challenging and rewarding. You’ll need to work within multiple computer systems simultaneously as you respond to questions or provide specific medication details / clinical information. It’s a fast paced, high volume environment where our members are counting on us to deliver these important, sometimes life - saving medications in an accurate and efficient manner.
The *Pharmacy Technician* is responsible for evaluating and authorizing approval of prior authorization pharmacy requests from prescribers received by telephone and/or fax using client criteria. Primary duties may include, but not limited to:
Determines appropriateness for medications. Communicates decision to physicians, physician's office staff, medical management staff and/or pharmacists.
Researches, resolves and documents prior authorization outcomes in pharmacy system.
Communicates selected prior authorization criteria, pharmacy benefit coverage and formulary alternatives to physicians, physician's office staff, medical management staff and/or pharmacists.
Escalates requests to Pharmacist when request requires extensive clinical review or denial.
Researches, resolves and documents physician or client inquiries and grievances and provides verbal or written results to client, prescriber, provider and/or management.
Verifies member information and inputs data for the pharmacists.
Educates members on pharmacy based rules related to prescriptions and medication resources or assistance programs.
Processes prior authorization requests from physicians’ offices and ensures compliance with Medicare requirements; informs relevant parties of all prior authorization determinations.
Provides resolution to grievances and appeals issues.
Maintains record keeping of prior authorizations, rebates, and monthly reports.
Requirements*:
Must be bilingual.
Requires High School diploma or GED, and 2 years of pharmacy experience.
Current National Certification and State Pharmacy Tech Certification based on applicable state(s) are required.
In-depth knowledge of specialty injectable prescription drugs, disease states, health plan formulary management techniques, medical terminology and current diagnostic and reimbursement coding (J/Q codes, ICD-9, CMS 1500, etc.).
Proficiency in Pharmacy computerized systems and software applications, as well as Windows-based applications and MS Office Product Suite.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills.
Ability to follow clinical criteria and instructions to approve prior authorization requests.
Preferred Qualifications*
Prior call center experience strongly preferred.
Medical terminology training, pharmaceutical terminology experience and/or experience in medical, insurance or pharmaceutical field are preferred.
Specialty or retail pharmacy industry experience, previous reimbursement experience, and/or working in a health plan/health care setting.
Advanced verbal and written communication skills
Team-oriented, customer service focused, and able to identify process improvements
Responsive, reliable and able to express assurance/confidence
Demonstrate strong research skills with the ability to evaluate, focus on the problem and find the resolution.
Understand the importance of timely work and effective planning.
Prioritizing and organizing workload in adherence to deadlines.
Desire and aptitude to assist a customer with escalated concerns and provide final resolutions.
Ability to respond to escalated concerns in a calm and professional manner in attempts to prevent further escalations.
Ability to multi-task with strong time management skills

The purpose of this role, is to create a safe, professional environment for patients to receive treatment. The CCHT is the first staff member that meets and greets patient on the treatment floor.
ABOUT SATELLITE HEALTHCARE
Satellite Healthcare, Inc. has been among the nation's leading not-for-profit providers of kidney dialysis and related services since 1974. Through its affiliated services, Satellite WellBound, Satellite Dialysis, and Satellite Research, Satellite Healthcare provides unparalleled early patient wellness education, personalized clinical services, and a complete range of dialysis therapy choices. In addition, Satellite Healthcare has a well-recognized, enduring commitment to philanthropy and community service, from funding millions of dollars in research grants to sponsoring kidney programs nationwide. Satellite Healthcare is committed to advancing the standard of chronic kidney disease care so patients can enjoy a better life.

At Satellite Healthcare (SHC), we work with Purpose at the heart of everything we do. It starts with our Mission to make life better for those with kidney disease and our Vision to be unsurpassed in our individualized experience, our quality, and our compassion. Our core Values round out our Purpose by defining how we choose to show up each day. As a member of the team, you will be invited to discover your own personal purpose at work and ways to activate that purpose to create a more fulfilling work-life for yourself. It is our hope and belief that, as you and your colleagues learn to courageously live and work by your purpose, you will find that it not only lifts your work and career, but the organization and the community of patients as well.

ABOUT THE ROLE
We are seeking a purpose-driven team member with a record of accomplishment, providing a safe and professional environment for patients to receive treatment. They will be the first team member to meet and greet patients on the treatment floor. Positive first impressions set the tone for family members; as well as, for patients in experiencing a more relaxed treatment that enhances treatment quality. Dialysis technicians at Satellite are compelled to make the patients feel comfortable once they enter our centers and throughout the course of their treatment. The technician will advocate for patients while they are at the unit, and effectively communicate with other team members any information pertinent in delivering quality care.

Our experienced technicians help boost the fulfillment and performance of progressive workplaces, by providing information, training on compliance and assisting with education for both staff and patients. This knowledge base, support and ability to train is arguably the most important role in the center.

The dialysis technician role is THE most important role who delivers or diminishes a positive patient experience and perceived “value” the patient receives.

ABOUT YOU
You will play a vital role to ensure that we deliver on our Mission to make life better for those with kidney disease and our Vision to be unsurpassed in our individualized experience, our quality, and our compassion. You approach your work with an indisputable sense of greater Purpose. You are patient-centric and thrive in environments that provide you fulfillment when enhancing the lives of those you care and serve. Lastly, you are high energy, love a challenge, are goal oriented, and gain deep satisfaction from building lifetime relationships.

WHAT YOU WILL GAIN

Relationships: You will work directly with a multi-disciplinary team who are just as passionate as you with making a difference in others’ lives. You will also work alongside servant leaders who look to support you in providing care that is unsurpassed by others in our industry.

Impact: You will provide care that will enable our patients to live a better life that meets their needs holistically.

Growth: You will receive many challenges that will enhance your professional skills and capabilities. You will work in an environment where fulfilling one’s aspirations is not necessarily a linear path, but more like a jungle gym with multiple options for development.

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS

Experience: Six (6) months of active hemodialysis patient care experience as a certified hemodialysis technician

Education: High School Diploma, G.E.D. certificate, or equivalent

License/Certifications:
BONENT (CHT)/NNCC (CCHT)/NNCO (CCNT) certification (per state regulations)
California Department of Public Health CHT certification (required only for CA locations)
Current CPR certification - American Heart Association

Description

Pet Specialists of Monterey (PSM), a new addition to the BluePearl family, is hiring an exceptional Registered Veterinary Technician to join our ICU team. If you enjoy patient care and working in a fast-paced, challenging, interesting, and collaborative environment, apply today! This is a full-time position that requires flexibility to work nights and weekends.

Join our team of professionals! We are seeking an RVT to share their skills and compassion in a new state-of-the-art facility located in beautiful Monterey, on the Central Coast of California. Our specialty practice is family-oriented, with a top-notch staff and experiences significant growth every year.

Do you work well under pressure in a fast-paced environment?
Would your peers describe you as patient, respectful, and compassionate?
Are you eager to make a difference for animals and provide premier patient care?

If you answered “yes” to these questions, we want to hear from you!

Responsibilities include: triage patients, room clients and patients, take an efficient and accurate history and vitals of patients, interact with clients, explain treatments, procedures, medications, and disease processes, give IM, IV, SQ injections, competent phlebotomist- from various veins and positions, able to place catheters, manage multiple patients, flow, and time management, relay phone messages to doctor and clients, accurately and efficiently administer advice to owners over the phone, critical care nursing, surgical assisting, anesthetic monitoring of critical cases, medical charting, and assisting veterinarian with procedures.

Why BluePearl?

Our passion is pets. We offer Trupanion pet insurance and discounts to our associates for pet treatments, procedures, and food.
We encourage you to grow with us. Our technicians are leveled by their skillset and move up in level as they gain more skills and experience. We are focused on developing our associates into leaders through talent development programs and leadership workshops. As a member of Mars Veterinary Health, our associates have endless opportunities to advance in his/her career.
In order to transform and lead the industry through innovative quality medicine and care, we understand the importance of continuous learning. We offer annual continuing education allowance, free continuing education sessions, our own BluePearl University for training, and our clinicians have access to over 2,000 medical journals.
We value your health and well-being as an associate by providing you with the following:
Health, dental, vision, and life insurance options.
Flexible work schedules.
Time to reset, rewind, and reflect through our paid time off and floating holiday plans.
A regional licensed social worker who can provide guidance, advice, and tips/tricks on how to maintain a healthy lifestyle while working in a fast-paced emergency and specialty care environment.
We promote a family-like culture in our hospitals. We are all in this together. We believe in working together to lead the industry by enriching lives through remarkable care for pets.

If you have been looking for a way to advance your career, apply today!

Job Summary:
This position is responsible for the operation and organization of the shipping, receiving, and warehousing departments in a 24/7 flexible packaging company. This position is overseen by department leads and reports to the Warehouse Manager. All employees are expected to follow and contribute to safe work practices.

SHIFT: M-F 1:00pm - 9:00pm

Essential Functions:
Receive, organize, and store inbound inventory. Make sure incoming material is properly marked. Inform the front office, if necessary, when it arrives.
Organize and store finished goods production. Checks to make sure materials are properly marked.
Ship finished goods to customers. Communicate with management about shipping schedule.
Organize pallet storage. Keep tracks of pallet count to make sure pallets are not being stolen.
Organize production scrap. Keep records of department totals for weekly reporting. When enough pallets are collected, call the scrap company for pick up.
Fill out all necessary paperwork for incoming and outgoing materials. Transfer them to the front office daily.
Inventory maintenance involving cycle counts, quarterly inventories, PO# creation, and data management in the ERP system
Organize warehouse area as best as possible. Communicate with the personnel in bag and press departments to ensure that the warehouse maintains organization. If problems arise, contact a member of management.
Work with the maintenance department to ensure forklifts are properly maintained.
As computer technology is integrated into the company, help keep track of inventory using the automated system.
Make sure safe work practices are followed. Suggest training and actions that could improve work place safety.
Use company truck for pick-ups, transfers, and deliveries
Additional Responsibilities:
Work overtime needed, including weekends, to meet department needs.
Help with emergency evacuation procedures.
Do various tasks necessary to ensure the department works efficiently.
Responsible for reporting any food safety issues
Responsible for complying with all GMP's
Qualifications:
Previous experience in shipping and receiving.
Knowledge of how to drive forklifts and unload trucks.
Excellent understanding of math.
Ability to work with management and individuals.
Clean DMV driving record
Basic computer skills necessary, experience with Microsoft Office applications.

Digital Fabrication Specialist:

Since our start in 1982 we have been pioneers in adapting state-of-the-art technology to problem-solving in construction, art and design. We have worked with internationally known artists, architects and engineers, using composite materials and advanced manufacturing techniques to address complex construction challenges; we have even worked on a project to create tools to measure dark matter. We have helped build blockbuster movie sets, rehabilitated a number of landmark historical buildings throughout the United States, and won numerous awards for the creative use of composite materials.

Most recently Kreysler & Associates has opened a new facility on Mare Island in Vallejo, California and is at the beginning of a new multi-year project with unique market opportunity.

Please consider joining our team and visit www.kreysler.com for more information.
Position Overview:
Kreysler & Associates’ Mare Island facility is looking for a Digital Fabrication Specialist to join our team and support our newly developed and proprietary fabrication process. The Digital Fabrication Specialist will be expected to become familiar with all aspects of using Kreysler & Associates’ equipment, software and materials to fabricate molds, patterns, and products. Preference will be given to those with proven success using Rhino, Powermill and operating a seven-axis CNC robot.

Ability to communicate and stick to timelines will be essential to finding success in this position as you will be responsible for the output and workflow of the digital fabrication element of our manufacturing process.

As a Digital Fabrication Specialist you will have opportunity to learn our proprietary process, contribute to a culture of continuous improvement and coordinate the movement of product through our manufacturing facility.
Requirements/Skills:
Supervising, scheduling, and operating CNC equipment
Ability to communicate effectively with team members
Fluency with CAD software, including Rhino, Powermill, Geomagic, and other software
Exceptional organization and ability to maintain file structure on our server
Ability to work in a production shop atmosphere as a team member
Ability to check machined part for accuracy
Ability to understand, schedule and execute on daily production plans ensuring the output of product
Responsibilities may include, but are not limited to:
Attending morning meetings and setting daily production goals
Understanding and relaying production needs based on project schedules
Creating toolpaths for parts based on daily schedules
Operating a 7-axis CNC robot
Preparing and distributing QC documents to ensure the fabrication of quality product
Identifying material needs for mold creation
Generating and distributing technical drawings
Responsibilities will always include:
Supporting others and promoting a positive work environment
Attention to detail
Respecting yourself and others
Practicing and enforcing safety best practices
Willingness to learn
Positive attitude
Benefits:
Health Insurance
Dental Insurance
Paid Time Off
Seven Paid Holidays
Simple IRA (eligible after one year of employment)
Opportunity to study and become a Certified Composite Technician (CCT)
\*\*All shifts available: day, swing and overnight\*\*

ORGANIZATION: *Conservation Society of California

Responds to radio calls and provides Basic First Aid / Life Support as needed. Upholds the mission and values established the Conservation Society of California (the “Zoo”) and adheres to policies and procedures as set forth by the Zoo.

_EMT related_*

SUMMARY: *
The Coatings Technician is a direct labor position within the Production Team whose main responsibilities are to process parts within the Twin Arc Spray room according to written processes and known practices. There are three levels of competency within this group:

· Technician I, can only perform these duties under supervision of skilled technician

· Technician II, ability to perform these duties with some supervision.

· Lead Technician III, person who has ability to perform all duties with limited or no supervision.
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES *include the following. Other duties may be assigned:
Safety First. Employee has been trained and is to follow all general safety requirements of Pentagon Technologies, as well as specific safety requirements within the Twin Arc Spray team. Employee should be safety conscience for their safety and the safety of those they work with. Proper use and care of the equipment they use and the safety equipment they wear. Employee will be trained on general safety requirements at time of hire, and specific requirements within this team during the first 90 days of his/her employ.

Employee is responsible to mask parts requiring coating process according to prints attached to traveler. Spraying part on surface requiring process. Detailing coating build up along tape edge and masked area. Maintain equipment. Change contact tips, guide line tips and feed line as required after inspection. Clean equipment with vacuum and air sprayer to reduce dust build up. Clean hoods of aluminum build up and dust. Empty dust collector drum of filtered dust and cyclone drum. Maintain fixtures in good working order.

Understand and follow operating procedures as assigned to the team to assure consistent, reliable, and timely processing of parts within this team.

Ability to perform under pressure, and the ability to bring to management in a clear, concise, and professional manner all potential conflicts in the performance of their duties.

Has an appreciation for timeliness, quality, and punctuality. This includes following all rules and regulations, including safety, attendance, breaks, time off, and etc. established by management.

Maintains organization and cleanliness of assigned areas.
SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES: *
The three positions listed, Technician I & II, have no supervisory responsibilities and Technician III has supervisory responsibilities.

Technician III Responsibilities, as assigned by the Production Manager, shall include but are not limited to, a complete and thorough understanding of the department functions. Must have good communication skills, comprehend and employ the Pentagon Technologies MIS system as it relates to their functions, have the ability manage time allocations of all assigned staff, and be able to manage minor conflicts within the team.
QUALIFICATIONS: *
Technician I, II, III

To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily within the skill sets listed above. Should have patience to perform work in quality manner, such as detailing parts to prevent rework do to scratches on coating as well as blast and finished surfaces. Should have patience in masking to assure tolerance according to specification of print. A willingness to learn and work with the department and other departments to provide on time work along with the requirements of engineering.
EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE: *
Technician I - High School education or GED, 6 months experience in masking and taping parts for grit texturizaiton, and chemical striping of depositions. Able to read and understand prints on areas of texturizaition and coating application. Able to identify damage to parts, especially critical surfaces, excessive part ware, etching, etc.

Technician II - High School education or GED, 1 year experience in masking and taping parts for grit texturizaiton, and chemical striping of depositions. Continuing education classes in quality or measurement. Able to read and understand prints on areas of texturizaition and coating application. Able to identify damage to parts, especially critical surfaces, excessive part ware, etching, etc. Ability to use a profilometer, micrometer, calipers and height gage to assure the application of coating. Basic computer skills and/or Robotic Operations.

Technician III - High School education or GED, 3 years experience in masking and taping parts for grit texturizaiton, and chemical striping of depositions. College level study in engineering working toward degree in either Engineering or Science. Able to read and understand prints on areas of texturizaition and coatings application. Able to identify damage to parts, especially critical surfaces, excessive part ware, etching, etc. Ability to use profilometer, micrometer, calipers and height gage to assure the application of coating.

Ability to run department to assure processes are followed and organize processing to achieve on time delivery of jobs. Basic computer knowledge and/or robotic programming techniques. Must be able to learn Robotic programming techniques.
LANGUAGE SKILLS: *
Ability to read and comprehend internal documents such as work order travelers, inventory records, logs and general company records.
MATHEMATICAL SKILLS *
Basic addition, subtraction, and multiplication skills in order to process inventory, counting, time allocation, and work hours.
REASONING ABILITY: *
Ability to apply common sense understanding to carry out instructions furnished in written, oral, or diagram form.
CERTIFICATES, LICENSES, REGISTRATIONS*
None Required.
PHYSICAL DEMANDS: *
The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.

Must pass company required physical/screening tests.

While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand, reach with hands and arms and be able to handle parts that weigh up to fifty pounds without assistance. Employee must be at least 5”4”, and be in good relative health. No accommodations can be made to enable individuals with major disabilities to perform these essential functions.
WORK ENVIRONMENT: *
The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job.

Must be able to work in a controlled confined, noisy environment that requires ear/eye protection at all time. Persons, who are sensitive to confine, noisy environments with such medical conditions as asthma, allergies, or extreme sensitivity to confine, noisy environment areas may not be considered as good candidates for this position.

The purpose of this role, is to create a safe, professional environment for patients to receive treatment. The CCHT is the first staff member that meets and greets patient on the treatment floor.
ABOUT SATELLITE HEALTHCARE
Satellite Healthcare, Inc. has been among the nation's leading not-for-profit providers of kidney dialysis and related services since 1974. Through its affiliated services, Satellite WellBound, Satellite Dialysis, and Satellite Research, Satellite Healthcare provides unparalleled early patient wellness education, personalized clinical services, and a complete range of dialysis therapy choices. In addition, Satellite Healthcare has a well-recognized, enduring commitment to philanthropy and community service, from funding millions of dollars in research grants to sponsoring kidney programs nationwide. Satellite Healthcare is committed to advancing the standard of chronic kidney disease care so patients can enjoy a better life.

At Satellite Healthcare (SHC), we work with Purpose at the heart of everything we do. It starts with our Mission to make life better for those with kidney disease and our Vision to be unsurpassed in our individualized experience, our quality, and our compassion. Our core Values round out our Purpose by defining how we choose to show up each day. As a member of the team, you will be invited to discover your own personal purpose at work and ways to activate that purpose to create a more fulfilling work-life for yourself. It is our hope and belief that, as you and your colleagues learn to courageously live and work by your purpose, you will find that it not only lifts your work and career, but the organization and the community of patients as well.

ABOUT THE ROLE
We are seeking a purpose-driven team member with a record of accomplishment, providing a safe and professional environment for patients to receive treatment. They will be the first team member to meet and greet patients on the treatment floor. Positive first impressions set the tone for family members; as well as, for patients in experiencing a more relaxed treatment that enhances treatment quality. Dialysis technicians at Satellite are compelled to make the patients feel comfortable once they enter our centers and throughout the course of their treatment. The technician will advocate for patients while they are at the unit, and effectively communicate with other team members any information pertinent in delivering quality care.

Our experienced technicians help boost the fulfillment and performance of progressive workplaces, by providing information, training on compliance and assisting with education for both staff and patients. This knowledge base, support and ability to train is arguably the most important role in the center.

The dialysis technician role is THE most important role who delivers or diminishes a positive patient experience and perceived “value” the patient receives.

ABOUT YOU
You will play a vital role to ensure that we deliver on our Mission to make life better for those with kidney disease and our Vision to be unsurpassed in our individualized experience, our quality, and our compassion. You approach your work with an indisputable sense of greater Purpose. You are patient-centric and thrive in environments that provide you fulfillment when enhancing the lives of those you care and serve. Lastly, you are high energy, love a challenge, are goal oriented, and gain deep satisfaction from building lifetime relationships.

WHAT YOU WILL GAIN

Relationships: You will work directly with a multi-disciplinary team who are just as passionate as you with making a difference in others’ lives. You will also work alongside servant leaders who look to support you in providing care that is unsurpassed by others in our industry.

Impact: You will provide care that will enable our patients to live a better life that meets their needs holistically.

Growth: You will receive many challenges that will enhance your professional skills and capabilities. You will work in an environment where fulfilling one’s aspirations is not necessarily a linear path, but more like a jungle gym with multiple options for development.

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS

Experience: Six (6) months of active hemodialysis patient care experience as a certified hemodialysis technician

Education: High School Diploma, G.E.D. certificate, or equivalent

License/Certifications:
BONENT (CHT)/NNCC (CCHT)/NNCO (CCNT) certification (per state regulations)
California Department of Public Health CHT certification (required only for CA locations)
Current CPR certification

Ensure equipment is accurately labeled with origination/destination information

Job Title: Garden Technician for Indoor Cannabis Cultivation Facility {State Flower}
Job Description:
* NOW HIRING * Full-time experienced Cultivation Staff for our cultivation facility.
INDUSTRY EXPERIENCE PREFERRED.
METRC experience is a plus!
Must be 21 or over to apply.
This is a full-time role in a rapidly expanding cultivation facility in San Francisco. We are offering competitive compensation commensurate with experience as well as health insurance and other benefits at 90 days.
Applicants should send a current resume and cover letter explaining their interest and qualifications for the job opportunity.
The Cultivation Technicians are responsible for assisting with all aspects of the company's cultivation operation from propagation to harvest. Essential functions include — but are not limited to — assisting the Cultivation Manager in various ways such as cleaning, cloning, transplanting, IPM applications, pruning plants, planting and resetting rooms as well as various miscellaneous tasks that fall under the day-to-day management of our gardens and their various individual departments.
Under the supervision of the Cultivation Manager, this team member will ensure that the facility is kept safe and compliant with OSHA standards as well as all state and local regulations at all times. This position will be responsible for following ALL Standard Operating Procedures (SOP’s) as they relate to various aspects of our cultivation and to maintain compliance within our facility at all times. Cultivation Technicians will be responsible for many of key day-to-day tasks that keep our facility operating smoothly and our production cycle on schedule, so it’s critical that they possess a positive mindset, a capacity to problem-solve, as well as a “team-first” mentality. We are a small family here at State Flower and we are looking for a few solid individuals to join our growing family.
We are looking for someone with cultivation experience, a mechanical inclination, and a "pay-it-forward" start-up mentality. We have developed a highly efficient cultivation system and are looking to identify a qualified person who can help us continue to implement this system as we expand our operations.
Essential Duties & Responsibilities
These include, but are not limited to, the following (other duties may be assigned):
General cleaning duties, e.g., scrubbing and sanitizing trays in propagation room, veg room and various flowering rooms; cleaning miscellaneous growing equipment to maintain protocols; transferring plants from one stage to the next; de-fanning plants, removing waste, weighing & tracking plant waste
Completes regularly scheduled quality assessment of plants for signs of pests/disease under the training of the Cultivation Manager.
Ensure the cultivation facility is consistently stocked with appropriate supplies at all times.
Ensures all equipment and systems (mechanical, lighting, fertigation/plumbing, etc) are properly maintained
Inventory procedures as they relate to proper plant counts, tracking information for inventory to ensure that our facility is always operating in compliance
Mop up spills, leaks and making sure safety signs are in place to caution employees on wet floors, oily surfaces, and other occupational hazards as soon as they are noticed.
Must wear Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) at appropriate times as this position may be exposed to splash hazards, high temperatures, and chemicals. Complete training will be provided upon hiring.
Transports trash and waste to disposal area.
Complies with safety requirements at all times.
GENERAL PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
Acts in a manner reflective of the company culture of high moral standards, innovation and continuous evolution, trust in the team, continuous improvement, and sustainable relationships.
Communicates, interacts, and works effectively with others; receptive to feedback and coaching; voices concern in a constructive manner.
Follow all safety protocols and policies; demonstrates commitment to safety first; communicates safety concerns; promotes a safe work environment based on established safety standards and training.
Present a professional image in appearance, actions, and words.
Demonstrate ownership, accountability, initiative, and quality of work.
Be a positive role model and demonstrate ethical behavior; build positive team relationships throughout your department and the rest of the organization.
Work scheduled shifts and show up on time and ready to work; record all time worked accurately, promptly, and honestly.
Understand and practice company values.
PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS: (Knowledge, Skills and Abilities)
Must understand and implement the rules, regulations, policies, and procedures of the company and the cultivation department.
Have a basic understanding of cannabis laws, rules and regulations set forth by the state; a pursuit to further their understanding and knowledge of the industry and the laws is appreciated and commendable.
Fundamental knowledge, as well as the ability to be taught and guided in areas related to cultivation with other areas being taught as the employee shows interest while still maintaining their capabilities as a cultivation technician.
Skill in analyzing potential problems with a plant or the product being processed.
Shows self-motivation/innovation and the ability to work well with all members of their staff and the company, as well as with their direct supervisor.
Ability to listen well and communicate effectively with various audiences, especially with direct supervisors and other co-workers.
Competencies
Must be at least 21 years of age.
Ability to add, subtract, multiply, and divide in all units of measure, using whole numbers, common fractions, and decimals.
Ability to solve practical problems.
Ability to interpret a variety of instructions furnished in written, oral, diagram, or schedule form.
Required Education and Experience
High school diploma or General Education Development (GED) or equivalent
Previous wash/sanitation experience within a manufacturing environment, highly preferred
Desirable Qualifications
Prior dishwashing experience
Prior janitorial experience
Prior trimming & cultivation experience
Supervisory Responsibility
None
Work Environment
While performing the duties of this job, the employee regularly works near moving mechanical parts. The employee is frequently exposed to herbal aromas, dust, and/or airborne particles. The employee occasionally works in high, precarious places.
Required Education and Experience
High school diploma or general education degree (GED) and one to three months related experience and/or training or equivalent combination of education and experience.
PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS
Regularly required to perform carrying, grasping, lifting, walking, standing, some bending/crouching, stooping, stretching, talking, hearing, seeing and repetitive motions.
Must be able to stand for extended periods of time while maintaining focus.
Ability to walk on uneven terrain.
Must be able to lift, carry, push, pull and balance up to 50 lbs. (100 lbs. with assistance) and must be able to do so with extreme care and caution when working with plants and product.
Must not be allergic to or have a fear of insects.
Work is performed in a fast-paced cannabis grow location.

SUMMARY: *
The Bead Blast Technician is a direct labor position within the Production Team whose main responsibilities are to process parts within the Bead Blast according to written processes and known practices. There are three levels of competency within this group.

· Technician I, can only perform these duties under supervision of skilled technician

· Technician II, ability to perform these duties with some supervision.

· Lead Technician III, person who has ability to perform all duties with limited or no supervision.
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES *include the following. Other duties may be assigned:
Safety First. Employee has been trained and is to follow all general safety requirements of Pentagon Technologies, as well as specific safety requirements within the Bead Blast team. Employee will be trained on general safety requirements at time of hire, and specific requirements within this team during the first 90 days of his / her employment. As the working environment involves noise, exposure to machinery with moving parts, dust, toxic or flammable substances, Personal Protective Equipment is required.

Employee is responsible to process customer supplied parts within the Bead Blast department according to known processes as specified by work order traveler instructions.

Must be proficient at operating a blasting nozzle.

Will blast parts with some deposition and surfacing parts to specific specifications.

Know proper blasting pressures as they relate to specifications for any particular part(s).

Ability to be able to handle delicate parts large or small without damaging.

Must lift parts weighing up to 75 pounds.

Possess knowledge of how parts should appear after blasting.

Will know what media to use on each job with an understanding of different metals.

Mechanical ability to disassemble parts inside the blasting cabinet.

Understand and follow operating procedures as assigned to the team to assure consistent, reliable, and timely processing of parts within this team. The Opportunity

Ulteig is seeking qualified candidates for the position of Commissioning Technician.The Commissioning Technician performs circuitry verification, apparatus, and metering testing. Any discrepancies are expected to be reported and addressed leaving the job site. Written reports about the project are to then be written after the completion of the job.

What You'll Do
Inspect, test, troubleshoot, perform start-up and collect data of low, medium and high voltage (to 500kV) electrical systems, and moderately complex metering and relay calibration, including:
Perform installation, commissioning, testing and maintenance of metering and protective relaying equipment, relaying schemes, DFR equipment, SCADA systems and associated communication equipment
Perform functional testing of communication and control circuits
Perform verification on CT and PT circuits
Perform maintenance on metering equipment
Analyze test data to diagnose malfunctions and present workable solutions
What We Expect from You
High school diploma or GED required; prefer an Associate’s degree from an accredited 2 year technical college in Electrical Power
Preferred 5 or more years of relevant power systems testing& maintenance experience within high voltage applications
Must have general PC skills
Must be able to work safely and adhere to all electrical safety procedures
Prefer knowledge of the CAISO and/or Utility metering standards
Must be competent in the use of the different Microsoft Office programs
Must be able to program various revenue meters (ION, SEL, TransData, etc.)
Must be able to read and understand electrical one-lines, three-lines and control schematics
Must be able to work alone or with a team
Must be a self-motivated, problem-solver
Must be able to pass a pre-employment drug test and periodic, unannounced random drug tests
Must be able to crawl, climb, stand and lift up to 75 lbs., with or without reasonable accommodations
Must be available for regular overnight travel (60-80% Travel)
Must have a valid driver’s license, and currently have and be able to maintain a good driving record
Ability to work regularly in the field which may vary from an outdoor environment exposed to any seasonal elements to inside working space which could vary widely in temperature to include occasional -0 and 100+ degree temperatures
Must have permanent authorization to work in the United States

For 75 years, we’ve built a culture focused on people– both our clients and our employees. We realize that a huge part of our success has relied heavily on the dedication and focus of our workforce; this is why we make investing in our employees a top priority. With more than 2,000 employees serving over 200 companies worldwide, we are following our mission of revolutionizing the way IT is deployed around the globe.
Job Overview*
The Move, Add, Change Technician is a part time role dedicated to relocation, deployment and support projects for Milestone Technologies. Projects will consist of disconnecting workstations and/or servers, relocating hardware to a new facility and reconnecting workstations and/or servers in a new environment.

Candidates should be self-starters, punctual, motivated/driven, pay attention to detail, are excited to learn and have the ability to work in a fast-paced environment. Candidates will need to work well under pressure on large, fast-paced projects with changing priorities. We are looking for an excellent team player with a positive, flexible demeanor, and the ability to operate with a sense of urgency. This position requires standing for long periods of time as well as repetitive bending, reaching, and heavy lifting.

Track project activities to which you are assigned

Troubleshoot layer 1 network issues
Accurately create/read and rack elevation drawing, patching matrices and layer 1 network topologies
Proficiently and accurately disconnect and reconnect PC workstations and peripherals in a timely manner
Ensure equipment is accurately labeled with origination/destination information

High School diploma or GED Required
Experience in a Data Center / Layer 1 troubleshooting

Ability to lift 50 pounds
Basic iOS/Android, Win OS Navigation skill

CompTIA A+ and CompTIA Server +

Pet Specialists of Monterey (PSM), a new addition to the BluePearl family, is hiring an exceptional Registered Veterinary Technician to join our ER team. If you enjoy patient care and working in a fast-paced, challenging, interesting, and collaborative environment, apply today! This is a full-time position working day shifts in our ER - we are looking for someone with flexibility to work weekends.

Join our team of professionals! We are seeking an RVT to share their skills and compassion in a new state-of-the-art facility located in beautiful Monterey, on the Central Coast of California. Our specialty practice is family-oriented, with a top-notch staff and experiences significant growth every year.

Do you work well under pressure in a fast-paced environment?
Would your peers describe you as patient, respectful, and compassionate?
Are you eager to make a difference for animals and provide premier patient care?

If you answered “yes” to these questions, we want to hear from you!

Responsibilities include: triage patients, room clients and patients, take an efficient and accurate history and vitals of patients, interact with clients, explain treatments, procedures, medications, and disease processes, give IM, IV, SQ injections, competent phlebotomist- from various veins and positions, able to place catheters, manage multiple patients, flow, and time management, relay phone messages to doctor and clients, accurately and efficiently administer advice to owners over the phone, critical care nursing, surgical assisting, anesthetic monitoring of critical cases, medical charting, and assisting veterinarian with procedures.

Why BluePearl?

Our passion is pets. We offer Trupanion pet insurance and discounts to our associates for pet treatments, procedures, and food.
We encourage you to grow with us. Our technicians are leveled by their skillset and move up in level as they gain more skills and experience. We are focused on developing our associates into leaders through talent development programs and leadership workshops. As a member of Mars Veterinary Health, our associates have endless opportunities to advance in his/her career.
In order to transform and lead the industry through innovative quality medicine and care, we understand the importance of continuous learning. We offer annual continuing education allowance, free continuing education sessions, our own BluePearl University for training, and our clinicians have access to over 2,000 medical journals.
We value your health and well-being as an associate by providing you with the following:
Health, dental, vision, and life insurance options.
Flexible work schedules.
Time to reset, rewind, and reflect through our paid time off and floating holiday plans.
A regional licensed social worker who can provide guidance, advice, and tips/tricks on how to maintain a healthy lifestyle while working in a fast-paced emergency and specialty care environment.
We promote a family-like culture in our hospitals. We are all in this together. We believe in working together to lead the industry by enriching lives through remarkable care for pets

If you have been looking for a way to advance your career, apply today!

JOB SUMMARY *
Identify and resolve technical and warranty issues including repair and replacement, mechanical and electrical troubleshooting, wiring or mechanical modifications to the MST Intelligent Transportation Systems.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS *
Maintains, troubleshoots and diagnoses Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS) technology installed on and off the revenue vehicles. Works closely with Automatic Vehicle Location (AVL) vendor to ensure the system is working at optimal performance. Works with the MST Electronic Technicians and Maintenance Department to ensure AVL system compatibility and integration with non-ITS vehicle systems. Works with County of Monterey IT department pertaining to the radio/data infrastructure at remote tower sites and coordinates assistance between AVL and County personnel.
Configures, tests, maintains, monitors, and troubleshoots end user voice/data software. Recommends and implements corrective hardware/software solutions. Maintains on-site inventory of spares and provides inventory reports. Coordinates warranty repair/replacements with vendors. Documents and reports software or hardware failure incidents, including repair, installation, removal and other work requests. Inspects, tests and maintains AVL data/voice systems, and associated wiring and cabling. Performs other duties as assigned.
KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS and ABILITIES *
Electronic systems maintenance, call records management systems, contact center management systems, call recording systems. Planning, installing, and troubleshooting voice/data cabling and wiring systems. Microsoft Office 365 applications. Communicate complex ideas and translate technical information into user-understandable terms with tact, patience and courtesy, both verbally and in writing. Work effectively in a team-oriented, collaborative environment, establishing and maintaining effective working relationships. Work with minimal supervision. Operate tools, components, peripherals, and testing accessories. Drive to various district locations as required. Prioritize and execute multiple tasks and projects. Read and interpret technical documentation and procedure manuals.
MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS & REQUIREMENTS *
Any combination of education and experience equivalent to an associate degree with a minimum of approximately three years professional and technical experience in telecommunication protocols. Class C driver’s license required.
